    RemoteSupportServiceImpl.REQUEST_PASSCODE, origin,
    rpPhoneVerification);  // ← ADD


Summary Table



|Location                                            |Problem                                                                                               |Fix                                                                                    |
|----------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|`checkPhoneVerified()` in `RemoteSupportServiceImpl`|Re-queries DB independently for `RpPhoneVerification`, gets null when BC4’s write isn’t visible to BC5|Accept `rpPhoneVerification` as parameter; eliminate internal re-query                 |
|`confirmPasscode()` in `RemoteProofingServiceImpl`  |Fetches `rpPhoneVerification` but never passes it to `checkPhoneVerified()`                           |Pass the already-fetched object into the method call                                   |
|`requestPasscode()` in `RemoteProofingServiceImpl`  |Same pattern as `confirmPasscode()`                                                                   |Same fix                                                                               |
|`@Transactional` class-level on both services       |BC5 opens its DB connection before BC4 commits, causing read isolation miss                           |Fixed structurally by eliminating the second query; no transaction config change needed|

The fix is two changed method signatures and two updated call sites. No infrastructure changes, no DB schema changes, no session management needed.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​
